					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Actually, test ROMs don't really point at exact place of a problem. They give a direction for search, but they can't detect a wide range of potential problems, and can give false reports, either giving you a false direction, or false sense of correctness (report OK while emulation is in fact wrong). There were threads on this forum with such cases.</div>

